Go-onCARE (CareCRUD V1) — Full System Architecture & Documentation
====================================================================


1. SYSTEM OVERVIEW
==================

Go-onCARE is a desktop clinic management system built with Python, PyQt6, and MySQL. It manages the full lifecycle of a healthcare clinic — from patient registration and appointment scheduling to clinical queues, billing/POS, HR management, and analytics — all within a single role-based desktop application.

Technology Stack:
  - Language:        Python 3.x
  - GUI Framework:   PyQt6 (Fusion style + QSS stylesheets)
  - Database:        MySQL via mysql-connector-python
  - Charts:          Custom QPainter-based widgets (no external chart libs)
  - Architecture:    Single-process desktop app, mixin-based backend
  - Connection:      localhost, database carecrud_db

Scale: ~30 Python files, ~8,500+ lines of Python, ~1,250 lines of QSS, 17 database tables, 8 views, 5 user roles.


2. HIGH-LEVEL ARCHITECTURE
===========================

    ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
    │                        main.py (Entry Point)                 │
    │         App → AuthWindow → login → MainWindow(role)          │
    └──────────┬──────────────────────────────────────┬────────────┘
               │                                      │
       ┌───────▼──────────┐                 ┌─────────▼──────────┐
       │   UI Layer        │                │   Backend Layer     │
       │  (PyQt6 Widgets)  │───calls───────>│  (AuthBackend)      │
       │                   │                │                     │
       │  auth_window.py   │                │  ┌── DatabaseBase ──┐
       │  main_window.py   │                │  │  base.py         │
       │  8 Page widgets   │                │  └──────────────────┘
       │  6 Dialog classes  │                │  ↑ inherited by all │
       │  chart_widgets.py │                │  AuthMixin (auth)   │
       │  styles.py        │                │  PatientMixin       │
       │  reports.py       │                │  EmployeeMixin      │
       │  2 QSS themes     │                │  AppointmentMixin   │
       └───────────────────┘                │  ClinicalMixin      │
                                            │  DashboardMixin     │
                                            │  AnalyticsMixin     │
                                            │  SettingsMixin      │
                                            │  SearchMixin        │
                                            └─────────┬──────────┘
                                                      │
                                            ┌─────────▼──────────┐
                                            │   MySQL Database    │
                                            │   carecrud_db       │
                                            │   17 tables         │
                                            │   8 views           │
                                            │   16 indexes        │
                                            └─────────────────────┘

The backend uses a mixin composition pattern — a single AuthBackend class inherits from 9 mixins + DatabaseBase, giving every page access to the entire API through one shared instance:

    class AuthBackend(DatabaseBase, AuthMixin, EmployeeMixin, PatientMixin,
                      AppointmentMixin, ClinicalMixin, DashboardMixin,
                      AnalyticsMixin, SettingsMixin, SearchMixin):
        pass


3. DATABASE SCHEMA (17 Tables)
===============================

3.1 Entity-Relationship Diagram
--------------------------------

     roles <──FK── users ──FK──> user_preferences
       │
       ├──FK── employees ──FK──> departments
       │          │
       │          ├──── leave_requests
       │          ├──── notifications
       │          │
       │          └──FK── appointments ──FK──> services
       │                     │       └── self-FK (recurring_parent_id)
       │                     │
       │                     ├──FK── queue_entries
       │                     │
       │                     └──FK── invoices ──FK──> payment_methods
       │                                │                discount_types
       │                                └──── invoice_items ──FK──> services
       │
       └──FK── patients ──FK──> discount_types
                  │
                  └──── patient_conditions ──FK──> standard_conditions

3.2 Lookup Tables (6)
----------------------

  Table                  Purpose                                           Seed Data
  ─────                  ───────                                           ─────────
  departments            9 departments (General Medicine, Cardiology,      9 rows
                         Dentistry, Pediatrics, Laboratory, Front Desk,
                         Management, Pharmacy, Human Resources)
  roles                  5 system roles                                    5 rows
  services               Medical services with price, category, active     13 rows
  payment_methods        Cash, GCash, Credit Card, Debit Card, Insurance   5 rows
  standard_conditions    21 common medical conditions for checklist         21 rows
  discount_types         Senior Citizen 20%, PWD 20%, Employee 10%         3 rows

3.3 Core Entity Tables (4)
---------------------------

  Table              Key Columns                                         Notes
  ─────              ───────────                                         ─────
  users              user_id, full_name, email (UNIQUE),                 Authentication & RBAC
                     password_hash, role_id (FK→roles),
                     must_change_password
  user_preferences   pref_id, user_id (FK→users),                       Per-user settings
                     pref_key, pref_value
  employees          employee_id, first_name, last_name,                 HR data; status =
                     role_id (FK→roles), department_id                   Active/On Leave/Inactive
                     (FK→departments), phone, email,
                     hire_date, status, employment_type,
                     salary, emergency_contact, notes
  patients           patient_id, first_name, last_name,                  Clinical data;
                     sex, date_of_birth, phone, email,                   auto-discount via FK
                     blood_type, emergency_contact,
                     discount_type_id (FK→discount_types),
                     status, notes

3.4 Junction Table
-------------------

  Table                Purpose
  ─────                ───────
  patient_conditions   Many-to-many between patients <-> standard_conditions

3.5 Transaction Tables (6)
---------------------------

  Table              Key Columns                                         Notes
  ─────              ───────────                                         ─────
  appointments       appointment_id, patient_id (FK),                    Status: Pending/
                     doctor_id (FK→employees), service_id                Confirmed/Cancelled/
                     (FK→services), appointment_date,                    Completed
                     appointment_time, status, notes,
                     cancellation_reason, reschedule_reason,
                     recurring_parent_id (self-FK),
                     reminder_sent
  queue_entries      queue_id, patient_id (FK), doctor_id                Status: Waiting/
                     (FK), appointment_id (FK), queue_time,              In Progress/Completed/
                     purpose, status, notes                              Cancelled
  invoices           invoice_id, patient_id (FK),                        Status: Unpaid/Partial/
                     appointment_id (FK), total_amount,                  Paid/Void
                     amount_paid, status, payment_method_id
                     (FK), notes, discount_type_id (FK)
  invoice_items      item_id, invoice_id (FK), service_id                Line-item detail
                     (FK), quantity, unit_price,
                     discount_percent, subtotal
  leave_requests     request_id, employee_id (FK),                       Status: Pending/
                     leave_type, start_date, end_date,                   Approved/Declined/
                     reason, status, hr_note                             Expired
  notifications      notification_id, employee_id (FK),                  Employee notification
                     title, message, is_read                             queue

3.6 Audit Table
----------------

  Table              Purpose
  ─────              ───────
  activity_log       log_id, user_email, action, record_type, detail, timestamp
                     — full audit trail of all system actions

3.7 Views (8)
--------------

  vw_employees, vw_patients, vw_appointments, vw_queue, vw_invoices,
  vw_doctor_performance, vw_monthly_revenue, vw_today_appointments,
  vw_top_services

3.8 Indexes (16)
-----------------

  On: users(email), employees(role_id, department_id, status),
  patients(status, discount_type_id), appointments(patient_id, doctor_id,
  date, status), queue_entries(patient_id, doctor_id, status),
  invoices(patient_id, appointment_id, status),
  activity_log(user_email, action, record_type, timestamp)


4. THE FIVE USER ROLES & THEIR ACCESS
=======================================

  Page               Admin    HR       Doctor   Cashier  Receptionist
  ────               ─────    ──       ──────   ───────  ────────────
  Dashboard          Full     Limited  Full     Full     Full
  Patients           CRUD     --       Own only View     CRUD + Merge
  Appointments       CRUD     --       Own only View     CRUD
  Clinical & POS     3 tabs   --       Queue    Billing  Billing
  Data Analytics     Full     --       Personal --       --
  Employees          HR view  HR view  --       --       --
  Activity Log       Full     Limited  --       --       --
  Settings           Full     --       --       --       --


5. COMPLETE USER FLOW — ROLE BY ROLE
======================================

5.1 Login Flow (All Users)
---------------------------

  App starts → AuthWindow (email + password)
    → backend.login(email, password)
    → If must_change_password=1 → ForcePasswordChangeDialog
    → Emit login_success(email, role, full_name)
    → MainWindow created with sidebar filtered by role
    → backend.set_current_user(email, role)

Every user sees a sidebar with only their permitted pages. A notification bell
appears for Doctor/Cashier/Receptionist (polls every 15 seconds). Leave
auto-expiry runs every 5 minutes.

5.2 Admin — Full System Control
---------------------------------

The Admin has unrestricted access to all 8 pages:

DASHBOARD — KPI cards (Today's Appointments, Active Patients, Revenue, Active
Staff), Today's Schedule table, Monthly Visits chart, Recent Activity feed.

PATIENTS — Full CRUD. Add/Edit via PatientDialog (name, sex, DOB, phone with
+63 prefix, email, blood type, conditions checklist, discount category, notes).
View profile with 4 tabs (Info, Appointments, Invoices, Queue History). Delete
with cascade warning. Merge duplicate patients.

APPOINTMENTS — Full CRUD. 5 date-based quick tabs (Today/Tomorrow/This Week/
This Month/All). Filters by doctor, status, and search. Create appointments
with conflict detection, date validation (today → end of next month), and
recurring scheduling (Daily/Weekly/Monthly × N). Sees billing status column.

CLINICAL & POS — All 3 tabs:
  - Patient Queue: Auto-syncs confirmed appointments into queue. Stat cards
    (Waiting/In Progress/Completed/Est. Wait). Doctor filter.
    Note: Admin cannot click "Call Next" — that's doctor-only.
  - Billing / POS: Create invoices with multi-line items, auto-loaded patient
    discounts (Senior 20%, PWD 20%, Employee 10%), payment methods, partial
    payments, print receipts, void invoices. Admin can override discount
    percentage on invoices.
  - Services & Pricing: Add/Edit services (name, price, category, active
    toggle). Bulk price update across all services.

DATA ANALYTICS — Full clinic analytics: KPI cards with month-over-month deltas
(Δ Revenue, Δ Patients, Δ Appointments), 4 pie charts (Patient Conditions,
Appointment Status, Revenue by Department, Demographics), Patient Retention
trend, Cancellation Rate trend, Doctor Performance ranking, Top Services
ranking, Monthly Revenue chart, Summary table with date range filter.

EMPLOYEES — The HREmployeesPage with 4 tabs:
  - Employees Tab: Stat cards (Total/Active/On Leave/Inactive/Avg Salary/
    Payroll), full CRUD with salary and emergency contact fields. Adding an
    employee auto-creates a user account (password = {role}123, forced change
    on first login).
  - Leave Management: View/Approve/Decline leave requests with HR notes.
    Approval automatically sets employee status to "On Leave" and sends a
    notification.
  - Payroll & Staffing: Department payroll summary, employment type breakdown.
  - User Accounts: Create/Delete user accounts, reset passwords.

ACTIVITY LOG — Full audit trail with filters: user email, action type, record
type, date range. Smart-refresh only reloads when new entries exist.

SETTINGS — Change own password. Manage discount types (add/edit/delete).
Database overview (row counts for all 17 tables). Cleanup tools: remove
completed appointments by date, remove cancelled appointments, remove inactive
patients, truncate individual tables.

5.3 HR — Employee & Leave Management
--------------------------------------

HR sees 3 pages: Dashboard, Employees, Activity Log.

DASHBOARD — Simplified: skips appointment/patient KPIs. Shows employee stats
and quick action "Manage Employees". Non-HR/Admin employees can submit leave
requests from their dashboard.

EMPLOYEES — Same HREmployeesPage as Admin with 4 tabs (Employees, Leave
Management, Payroll & Staffing). No User Accounts tab — that's Admin-only.

ACTIVITY LOG — Restricted to Login activity from Doctor & Receptionist roles
only.

5.4 Doctor — Clinical Workflow
-------------------------------

Doctor sees 5 pages: Dashboard, Patients, Appointments, Clinical & POS, Data
Analytics.

DASHBOARD — Full KPIs + "My Schedule" quick action. Can submit leave requests.

PATIENTS — Filtered to only their own patients (those with appointments under
this doctor). View profiles. No add/edit/delete.

APPOINTMENTS — Filtered to own appointments only. Doctor is auto-selected when
creating new appointments. Full edit capability on own appointments.

CLINICAL & POS — Queue tab only. Sees the "Call Next" button to call the next
waiting patient. Can edit queue entries (update status to In Progress/Completed,
add notes).

DATA ANALYTICS — Personal KPIs only: Total Appointments, Completed, Cancelled,
Personal Revenue, Completion Rate, own monthly revenue chart and breakdown table.

5.5 Cashier — Billing & Patient View
--------------------------------------

Cashier sees 4 pages: Dashboard, Patients, Appointments, Clinical & POS.

DASHBOARD — Full KPIs. Can submit leave requests.

PATIENTS — Can view patient list but no action buttons (no add/edit/delete).

APPOINTMENTS — Can view all appointments and filter them, but no edit actions
and no billing column.

CLINICAL & POS — Billing tab only. Create invoices, process payments, print
receipts, void invoices. Discount percentage is locked to the patient's
registered discount type.

5.6 Receptionist — Front Desk Operations
------------------------------------------

Receptionist sees 4 pages: Dashboard, Patients, Appointments, Clinical & POS.

DASHBOARD — Full KPIs + quick actions "+ New Appointment" and "+ New Patient".
Can submit leave requests.

PATIENTS — Full CRUD including add, edit, delete, and merge duplicate patients.
This is the primary patient-facing role.

APPOINTMENTS — Full CRUD. Create, edit, cancel appointments. Recurring
scheduling supported.

CLINICAL & POS — Billing tab only. Same as Cashier but can also void invoices.


6. KEY DATA FLOWS
===================

6.1 Patient Registration → Appointment → Queue → Invoice
-----------------------------------------------------------

  Receptionist adds patient (PatientDialog)
    → INSERT patients + patient_conditions
    → log_activity("Create", "Patient")

  Receptionist creates appointment (AppointmentDialog)
    → Conflict check → INSERT appointments
    → log_activity("Create", "Appointment")

  Auto-sync (every 10s) or manual
    → sync_today_appointments_to_queue()
    → Confirmed appointments → INSERT queue_entries (Waiting)

  Doctor clicks "Call Next"
    → Oldest Waiting → status = "In Progress"
    → Doctor completes → status = "Completed"

  Cashier creates invoice (NewInvoiceDialog)
    → Patient discount auto-loaded
    → Line items (service × qty × discount)
    → INSERT invoices + invoice_items
    → Payment → UPDATE amount_paid → status Partial/Paid

6.2 Leave Request Flow
------------------------

  Employee → Dashboard → "Request Leave"
    → INSERT leave_requests (Pending)

  HR → Leave Management → Approve
    → leave_requests status = "Approved"
    → employees status = "On Leave"
    → INSERT notifications (to employee)

  Timer (every 5 min) → auto_expire_leaves()
    → Past end_date + Approved → "Expired"
    → Employee status → "Active"

6.3 Employee → Auto User Account
----------------------------------

  Admin/HR adds employee
    → INSERT employees
    → AUTO: INSERT users (password = "{role}123", must_change_password=1)
    → First login → ForcePasswordChangeDialog


7. BACKEND API SUMMARY (100+ Methods across 9 Mixins)
=======================================================

  Mixin              File                   Methods   Responsibility
  ─────              ────                   ───────   ──────────────
  DatabaseBase       backend/base.py        10        DB connection, fetch(), exec(),
                                                      shared helpers, activity logging
  AuthMixin          backend/auth.py        10        Login, password management,
                                                      user account CRUD
  PatientMixin       backend/patients.py    8         Patient CRUD, profiles, merge,
                                                      doctor-filtered patients
  EmployeeMixin      backend/employees.py   25+       Employee CRUD, HR stats, payroll,
                                                      leave system, notifications
  AppointmentMixin   backend/appointments.py 9        Appointment CRUD, conflict
                                                      detection, recurring scheduling
  ClinicalMixin      backend/clinical.py    14        Queue management, invoices,
                                                      payments, services
  DashboardMixin     backend/dashboard.py   3         KPI aggregation, upcoming
                                                      appointments, monthly trends
  AnalyticsMixin     backend/analytics.py   15        Revenue analytics, doctor
                                                      performance, demographics, trends
  SettingsMixin      backend/settings.py    11        DB cleanup, conditions/discounts
                                                      management, table counts
  SearchMixin        backend/search.py      1         Global search across patients,
                                                      appointments, employees

7.1 DatabaseBase — backend/base.py
-----------------------------------

  Method                        Description
  ──────                        ───────────
  set_current_user(email, role) Sets session identity for logging
  _get_connection()             Returns (or creates) mysql.connector connection
  fetch(sql, params, one)       Executes SELECT → list[dict] or single dict
  exec(sql, params)             Executes INSERT/UPDATE/DELETE → lastrowid or rowcount
  exec_many(queries)            Runs multiple statements in single transaction
  _get_employee_name()          Looks up current user's employee full name
  _lookup_patient_id(name)      Resolves "first last" → patient_id
  _lookup_role_id(role_name)    Resolves role name → role_id
  log_activity(action, ...)     Inserts into activity_log
  get_latest_log_id()           Returns max log_id for smart refresh
  get_activity_log(limit, ...)  Filtered activity log retrieval
  close()                       Closes the MySQL connection

7.2 AuthMixin — backend/auth.py
---------------------------------

  Method                            Description
  ──────                            ───────────
  login(email, password)            Returns (success, role, full_name, message,
                                    must_change_password)
  clear_must_change_password(email) Clears the forced-change flag
  update_own_password(email, old, new) Changes password with verification
  force_change_password(email, new) Sets new password + clears flag
  get_all_user_accounts()           Admin: lists all user accounts
  admin_create_user_account(data)   Admin: creates user (must_change=1)
  admin_reset_password(user_id, new) Admin: resets any password
  admin_delete_user_account(user_id) Admin: deletes user account
  get_user_full_name(email)         Returns display name
  get_all_roles()                   Returns list of role names

7.3 PatientMixin — backend/patients.py
----------------------------------------

  Method                            Description
  ──────                            ───────────
  get_patients()                    Full patient list with conditions, discount, last visit
  get_patient_full_profile(id)      Returns {info, appointments, invoices, queue}
  add_patient(data)                 Inserts patient + syncs patient_conditions
  update_patient(patient_id, data)  Updates patient + re-syncs conditions
  delete_patient(patient_id)        Cascading delete of all related records
  merge_patients(keep_id, remove_id) Transfers all FK references then deletes
  get_patients_for_doctor(email)    Distinct patients with appointments under doctor
  get_active_patients()             Simple [{patient_id, name}] for dropdowns

7.4 EmployeeMixin — backend/employees.py
------------------------------------------

  Method                            Description
  ──────                            ───────────
  get_employees(detailed)           Employee list; optional salary/emergency fields
  get_employees_detailed()          Shortcut for get_employees(detailed=True)
  get_leave_employees()             Currently on-leave employees
  get_hr_stats()                    {total, doctors, active, on_leave, inactive,
                                    avg_salary, total_payroll}
  get_payroll_summary()             Department-level salary aggregation
  get_employment_type_counts()      Full-time / Part-time / Contract breakdown
  update_employee_salary(id, sal)   Updates salary field
  check_duplicate_phone(phone, id)  Prevents duplicate phone numbers
  add_employee(data)                Inserts employee + auto-creates user account
  update_employee(id, data)         Updates employee + syncs users table
  delete_employee(id)               Cascading delete of all related records
  get_employee_stats()              Active/On Leave/Inactive counts
  get_department_counts()           Per-department employee counts
  get_employee_performance(id)      {total_appts, completed, revenue}
  get_employee_appointments(id)     All appointments for an employee
  get_employee_id_by_email(email)   Resolves email → employee_id
  submit_leave_request(data)        Creates leave request
  get_pending_leave_requests()      HR view of pending requests
  get_all_leave_requests()          All leave requests
  get_my_leave_requests(id)         Employee's own leave history
